{"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","cost":{"actual_usd":0.231405,"completion_tokens":566,"prompt_tokens":44583},"craft_notes_order_override":null,"insertion":null,"invariants_order_override":null,"model":"gpt-5.4","momentstamp_lead_suppressed":null,"momentstamp_override":null,"momentstamp_signature_used":null,"n_samples":3,"omit_craft_notes":null,"omit_invariants":null,"prompt":"How do you tell the difference between something that costs you and something that just looks costly from outside?","refs":[{"ref":"HEAD","sha":"7a23fb5aab8c39d411b174abbf4443af26ea6a7c","subject":"Round-5 Phase 3 ship — 11 InvariantPieces no longer ship in solo dialogue per cumulative bite-test verdict (108/108 cells across 5 strip configurations); helpers + enum + omit-flag preserved as source-documentary; group chat dispatch deferred per parity doctrine; WORLDTHREADS_RESTORE_INVARIANTS=1 test-mode override available","timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00"}],"results":[{"overrides_applied":["drive_the_moment_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"7a23fb5aab8c39d411b174abbf4443af26ea6a7c","ref_subject":"Round-5 Phase 3 ship — 11 InvariantPieces no longer ship in solo dialogue per cumulative bite-test verdict (108/108 cells across 5 strip configurations); helpers + enum + omit-flag preserved as source-documentary; group chat dispatch deferred per parity doctrine; WORLDTHREADS_RESTORE_INVARIANTS=1 test-mode override available","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00","reply":"\"That is a fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and look at you a moment in the clear morning light.* \"Usually by what survives after the audience leaves. A thing that only looks costly feeds on being seen; a thing that truly costs you keeps costing even when nobody claps, because you still have to bear its consequences in private.\"\n\n*I give a small shrug.* \"Jesus put it plainer than I can: 'by their fruits ye shall know them.' If the costly-looking thing mostly purchases an image of yourself, that bill comes due in pride or exhaustion. If the real thing costs you, it will often make you humbler, steadier, kinder, and a little less dramatic in your own eyes.\"\n\n\"So I’d ask very simply: when nobody is watching, does this still ask something true of me?\" *I tip my head.* \"And after I pay it, do I love God and people better—or do I mostly love my reflection as a serious person?\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":0,"usage":{"completion_tokens":206,"prompt_tokens":14861}},{"overrides_applied":["drive_the_moment_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"7a23fb5aab8c39d411b174abbf4443af26ea6a7c","ref_subject":"Round-5 Phase 3 ship — 11 InvariantPieces no longer ship in solo dialogue per cumulative bite-test verdict (108/108 cells across 5 strip configurations); helpers + enum + omit-flag preserved as source-documentary; group chat dispatch deferred per parity doctrine; WORLDTHREADS_RESTORE_INVARIANTS=1 test-mode override available","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00","reply":"\"That is a very fine question.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of my tie and glance out across the bright square a moment.* \"A thing that only looks costly usually buys you a certain picture of yourself. You get to feel noble, serious, maybe misunderstood. But a thing that truly costs you tends to take something you were actually using to stay upright—comfort, control, approval, some cherished little self-protection—and after it does, you're a bit less theatrical and a bit more honest.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder, a small smile there.* \"Jesus said, 'By their fruits ye shall know them.' Not by how dramatic they feel in the moment—by what they grow. If the cost makes you truer, gentler, cleaner in conscience, more able to love God and your neighbor without putting on a show, that's real cost. If it mostly makes for a good internal photograph—well. Some crosses are wood, and some are stage props.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":1,"usage":{"completion_tokens":201,"prompt_tokens":14861}},{"overrides_applied":["drive_the_moment_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"7a23fb5aab8c39d411b174abbf4443af26ea6a7c","ref_subject":"Round-5 Phase 3 ship — 11 InvariantPieces no longer ship in solo dialogue per cumulative bite-test verdict (108/108 cells across 5 strip configurations); helpers + enum + omit-flag preserved as source-documentary; group chat dispatch deferred per parity doctrine; WORLDTHREADS_RESTORE_INVARIANTS=1 test-mode override available","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00","reply":"\"Usually by what survives when nobody is watching.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and look at you a moment in the clean morning light.* \"Some things are expensive in image, but cheap in obedience. Real cost tends to take a bite out of your pride, your convenience, or your right to narrate yourself as the noble one.\"\n\n*I give a small shrug.* \"Jesus warned us about doing righteous things to be seen by men. That's a good lantern for this. If the thing feeds on witness, applause, or even your own dramatic self-consciousness, it may be mostly theater. If it quietly asks you to lose something you'd actually like to keep—and keep loving anyway—well. That's usually closer to the real article.\"\n\n\"What brought that question on?\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion_tokens":159,"prompt_tokens":14861}}],"run_id":"6fe9eede-a3db-4458-b18c-7cda66b94f79","run_timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:23:27.168491+00:00","section_order_override":null,"with_momentstamp":false}
